# Titan Aurora — World-Class Portfolio Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the transformation of the current portfolio into a "Titan Aurora" themed masterpiece, designed to impress recruiters at top-tier companies like Google and Microsoft. We will leverage advanced React patterns, Framer Motion, and high-end CSS to create a disruptive, premium experience.

## Design Vision
- **Theme**: Obsidian Aurora (Deep noir + Electric Cyan + Royal Purple + Warm Gold).
- **Aesthetic**: Premium glassmorphism, depth-focused layouts, and organic motion.
- **Target**: High-end software engineering roles (Senior/Architect level).

![Titan Aurora Mockup](file:///C:/Users/kymeu/.gemini/antigravity/brain/a4d907e0-a32c-4c51-af4d-edf7b90ae575/titan_aurora_portfolio_hero_1776760125778.png)

## Proposed Changes

---

### [Refining the Design System]
Enhance the core CSS tokens to support elite-level aesthetics.

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///c:/Apps/spark-portfolio-main/src/index.css)
- Implement more complex gradients (multi-stop).
- Add "Aurora" specific keyframes for organic, varied movement.
- Refine `.glass` and `.glass-strong` with better backdrop filters and box-shadows.

---

### [Immersive Hero & Background]
Upgrade the initial impact of the site.

#### [MODIFY] [AuroraBackground.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/spark-portfolio-main/src/components/portfolio/AuroraBackground.tsx)
- Add mouse-parallax to the aurora blobs for a sense of depth.
- Enhance the grain layer for a cinematic texture.

#### [MODIFY] [Hero.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/spark-portfolio-main/src/components/portfolio/Hero.tsx)
- Upgrade the `Typewriter` to be more fluid.
- Implement "Staggered Reveal" for headings (letter-by-letter spring animation).
- Add a "magnetic field" to the hero section that subtly influences nearby text.

---

### [Advanced Interactive Components]
Increase the "tactile" feel of the interface.

#### [MODIFY] [CustomCursor.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/spark-portfolio-main/src/components/portfolio/CustomCursor.tsx)
- Create an "Intelligent Cursor" that reacts to different element types (e.g., changes to "View" on projects, "Link" on socials).
- Add a "speed" based lag effect for a fluid, high-end feel.

#### [MODIFY] [Projects.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/spark-portfolio-main/src/components/portfolio/Projects.tsx)
- Refine the `TiltCard` with even smoother physics.
- Add a "Glare" effect that follows the cursor across the card.

---

### [Professional Polish]
Ensure the details meet Google/Microsoft standards.

#### [MODIFY] [Experience.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/spark-portfolio-main/src/components/portfolio/Experience.tsx)
- Implement a "Vertical Timeline" with scroll-triggered line growth.
- Use glassmorphic nodes for milestones.

#### [MODIFY] [Navbar.tsx](file:///c:/Apps/spark-portfolio-main/src/components/portfolio/Navbar.tsx)
- Ensure the navbar uses a "Dock" metaphor for mobile.
- Add active link highlighting with a sliding underline animation.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `npm run lint` to ensure code quality.
- `npm run build` to verify production readiness and image optimization.

### Manual Verification
- **Visual Audit**: Verify the aurora blobs move organically without jitter.
- **Interactive Check**: Test the "Magnetic" pull on various screen sizes.
- **Accessibility**: Ensure contrast ratios on glass elements remain readable.
- **Cursor Check**: Confirm the cursor transforms correctly over buttons and cards.
